 not so long ago, it seemed that no one had anything to say about the Arab-Israeli conflict. Then, all at once, apparently a forest of views flourished. The verbosity was scarcely surprising. Some people have been waiting for centuries for their chance to express themselves on this topic and now, as Arno Mayer observed in The Persistence of the Old Regime, they were given "the chance to reason their way through a crisis that had always been compelling in its symbolic and spiritual aspects
